ast live and 24/7 on DStv channel 198 and GOtv Max and Jolli packages on channel 29, with the live eviction shows and weekly highlights aired on Africa Magic Showcase, Africa Magic Urban and Africa Magic Family. DStv viewers will also follow the drama this season with the DStv Now app on a smartphone, tablet or laptop Vanguard It is no longer news that the Big Brother Naija Season 5 will kick off July 19, 2020. What may, however, be newsworthy is the fact that all potential Housemates are in quarantine ahead of the premiere. July 2, 2020 In "Entertainment" By Ayo Onikoyi It was yet another intense week on the BBNaija Pepper Dem Reunion - maybe even more intense than the ones before it. Ebuka, the ultimate table shaker, delved into the romantic and near-romantic relationships in the house and as you would expect, there was DRAMA! No love… July 12, 2020 In "Entertainment" Following the success of the fourth season of the biggest and most viewed event on African television, Big Brother Naija, MultiChoice Nigeria has announced that the fifth season of the show will premiere in July 2020. May 20, 2020 In "News"